# BMT AI OS — Container Secrets Injection Template
#
# BMTOS-21 | Epic: BMTOS-EPIC-3 (OS Foundation & Infrastructure)
#
# WARNING: This is NOT an actual .env file used at runtime.
# It documents how secrets are injected into containers.
#
# ============================================================================
# SECURITY MODEL
# ============================================================================
#
# BMT AI OS NEVER passes secrets as environment variables. Environment vars
# are visible in `docker inspect`, /proc/*/environ, and log output — all of
# which violate security best practices.
#
# Instead, secrets are:
#   1. Stored as individual files under /etc/bmt-ai-os/secrets/ (0600, root)
#   2. Bind-mounted into containers at /run/secrets/ (read-only)
#   3. Read by application code from /run/secrets/<KEY>
#
# This mirrors Docker Swarm secrets and Kubernetes secret volume mounts,
# but works on a single-node Docker Compose deployment.
#
# ============================================================================
# SECRET LIFECYCLE
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Initialize:
#      sudo secrets-manager.sh init
#
# 2. Store a secret:
#      sudo secrets-manager.sh set OPENAI_API_KEY sk-...
#
# 3. Inject into service mount directory:
#      sudo secrets-manager.sh inject ollama
#
# 4. Start stack with security overlay:
#      docker compose \
#        -f bmt-ai-os/ai-stack/docker-compose.yml \
#        -f bmt-ai-os/runtime/security/container-security.yml \
#        up -d
#
# 5. Inside the container, the application reads:
#      /run/secrets/OPENAI_API_KEY   -> contains "sk-..."
#
# ============================================================================
# SECRET-TO-SERVICE MAPPING
# ============================================================================
#
# Secret Key               Mounted Into          Path Inside Container
# ----------------------   -------------------   -------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY           ollama                /run/secrets/OPENAI_API_KEY
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY        ollama                /run/secrets/ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# GOOGLE_API_KEY           ollama                /run/secrets/GOOGLE_API_KEY
# MISTRAL_API_KEY          ollama                /run/secrets/MISTRAL_API_KEY
# GROQ_API_KEY             ollama                /run/secrets/GROQ_API_KEY
# CHROMA_AUTH_CREDENTIALS  chromadb              /run/secrets/CHROMA_AUTH_CREDENTIALS
#
# ============================================================================
# READING SECRETS IN APPLICATION CODE
# ============================================================================
#
# Python example:
#   from pathlib import Path
#   def read_secret(name: str) -> str | None:
#       path = Path(f"/run/secrets/{name}")
#       return path.read_text().strip() if path.exists() else None
#
# Shell example:
#   API_KEY=$(cat /run/secrets/OPENAI_API_KEY 2>/dev/null || true)
#
# ============================================================================
# DO NOT put real secrets below this line. This file is committed to git.
# ============================================================================
